23/03/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The country's chief negotiator with the EU, Vladimir Drobnjak, said on Wednesday (22 March) that he expects the EU screening process -- meant to determine whether Croatia's laws are harmonised with those of the Union -- to be completed in October. Speaking to the American Chamber in Zagreb, Drobnjak said more would be known about the pace of the process after Finland takes over the rotating EU presidency in July. 
In other news Wednesday, the Croatian government endorsed a new bill that reforms the security services. The current Intelligence Agency and Counterintelligence Agency would merge into one new structure, the Security and Intelligence Agency. (HINA, HRT - 22/03/06)
